{"ID":270328, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"328\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs327.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs329.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 328<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">The first principles of the Gospel,<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> as I believe, are, faith, repentance, baptism for the remission\n  of sins,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> with the promise of the Holy Ghost.<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Look at Heb. 6:1 contradictions&mdash;&ldquo;Therefore leaving the principles of the doctrine of Christ,\n  let us go on unto perfection.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> If a man leaves the principles of the doctrine of Christ, how can he\n  be saved in the principles? This is contradiction. I don&rsquo;t believe it. I will render it as it should\n  be&mdash;&ldquo;Therefore not leaving the principles of the doctrine of Christ, let us go on unto perfection, not\n  laying again the foundation of repentance from dead works, and of faith toward God, of the doctrine\n  of baptisms, and of laying on of hands, and of resurrection of the dead, and of eternal judgment.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Kingdom of God<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">It is one thing to see the kingdom of God, and another thing to enter into it.<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> We must have a\n  change of heart<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> to see the kingdom of God, and subscribe the articles of adoption to enter therein.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">No man can receive the Holy Ghost without receiving revelations.<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> The Holy Ghost is a\n  revelator.<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Punishments Await this Generation<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">I prophesy, in the name of the Lord God<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> of Israel, anguish and wrath<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> and tribulation and the\n  withdrawing of the Spirit of God from the earth<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> await this generation, until they are visited with\n  utter desolation.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> This generation is as corrupt<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> as the generation of the Jews that crucified Christ;<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span>\n  and if He were here to-day, and should preach the same doctrine He did then, they would put Him\n  to death. I defy all the world to destroy the work of God;<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> and I prophesy they never will have\n  power to kill me till my work is accomplished,<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> and I am ready to die.<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"wideEllipse\">* * *<\/p>\n\n  <div class=\"topic \">Temporal Economy&mdash;Care of the Poor<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">The temporal economy of this people should be to establish and encourage manufactures, and\n  not to take usury<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> for their money. I do not want to bind the poor here to starve.<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> Go out into the\n  country and into the neighboring cities, and get food, and gird up your loins, and be sober.<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> When\n  you get food, return, if you have a mind to.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110165\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110165)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110165)\">Heb. 5:12<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117195\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117195)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117195)\">A of F 1:4<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111830\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111830)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111830)\">Alma 7:14<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113314\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113314)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113314)\">D&amp;C 19:31<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114323\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114323)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114323)\">D&amp;C 68:25<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116668\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116668)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116668)\">D&amp;C 138:33<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108939\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108939)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108939)\">Acts 2:33<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111330\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111330)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111330)\">2 Ne. 31:18<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115153\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115153)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115153)\">D&amp;C 100:8<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110170\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110170)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110170)\">Heb. 6:1<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110174\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110174)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110174)\">Heb. 6:1-2<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108638\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108638)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108638)\">John 3:3-5<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div 